100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 18, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing efforts to promote peace and stability in post-World War I Europe. Meanwhile, tensions escalated in the Middle East as the British government faced increasing unrest in Palestine, following the rise of nationalist sentiments among Arab populations. In the United States, the automotive industry continued its rapid expansion, with Ford announcing plans for a new assembly plant aimed at boosting production.
